                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="18773" author="luke" created="Tue, 25 Jul 2006 10:49:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Carlos has added log4j to the parent pom (with optional=true) since this issue was rasied. I&apos;ve removed it from the core pom.xml without any obvious problems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19170" author="carlos" created="Tue, 22 Aug 2006 03:18:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve reverted luke&apos;s change. log4j is still required at runtime (although optional) for directory tests&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="31225" author="ronaldtm" created="Thu, 24 Jan 2008 11:40:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it&apos;s optional, why can&apos;t it be marked as &apos;optional&apos;? and if it is used only on unit testing (are &apos;directory tests&apos; unit tests?), why can&apos;t its scope changed to &apos;test&apos;?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, Spring-Security-Core-2.0-M1 still retains a hard dependency on log4j.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
